-- PPF Is Interested in Greek State Gas Assets, E15 Reports
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-05-04T07:45:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/ppf-is-interested-in-greek-state-gas-assets-e15-reports.html
PPF Group NV, a Czech private-equity
firm, is taking part in bidding for DEPA SA, the Greek state gas
utility, which may be worth as much as 50 billion koruna ($2.6
billion),  E15  reported, citing unidentified people familiar with
the matter.  PPF, which is in the second round of the sale together with
13 other companies, declined to comment, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
